	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="R 6457-71 (15)"/>
			<p><!--{{Alexander Kirk}}, (Telegramm), Berlin, 1.3.1940, S. 1:</p>
      <p>Records of the Department of State relating to internal affairs of Poland 1916-1944,
        Washington 1981 (Mikrofilm-Edition): Dokument 860C.4016/???./p--></p>
			<p>It is learned that the some 1200 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews </term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575" type="subject">removed </term>from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3083829/szczecin.html">Stettlin</placeName> have been <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575" type="subject">settled</term> in three small towns in the
				neighborhood of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> where they are said to be now living
				under <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">conditions </term>of considerable hardship and
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-848" type="subject">poverty</term>.</p>
			<p>According to reliable <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-220" type="subject">information</term> the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">order</term> for the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">deportation</term> of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3089033/pila.html">Schneidemuhl</placeName> was issued by the same local authority who was
				responsible for the action taken in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3083829/szczecin.html">Stettin</placeName>. An <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-339" type="subject">arrangement</term> has been tentatively concluded
				whereby the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3089033/pila.html">Schneidemuhl</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> will not be sent to Eastern <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> as has been the case with those from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3083829/szczecin.html">Stettin</placeName> but will be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-575" type="subject">transferred</term> to other parts of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">Reich</term>.</p>
